    </table>

    <table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%">
    <tr>
        <td id="descriptionArea">
            <p>When the user rapidly clicks on the <b>cross (close) button</b> in the popup during NASS ePayment flow, the button intermittently becomes unresponsive.</p>

<p>In this state, if the user then clicks on the <b>confirm button</b>, the system incorrectly navigates to the <b>NASS ePayment order description page</b>, instead of maintaining the expected popup behavior or properly closing it.</p>

<h2><a name="StepstoReproduce%3A"></a>Steps to Reproduce:</h2>

<ol>
	<li>Go to FastPay Personal → NASS ePayment</li>
	<li>Proceed until the popup appears (confirm/cancel popup)</li>
	<li>Rapidly click on the <b>cross (X) button</b> multiple times</li>
	<li>Observe that the cross button becomes unresponsive</li>
	<li>Now click on <b>Confirm button</b></li>
</ol>


<h2><a name="ActualResult%3A"></a>Actual Result:</h2>

<ul>
	<li>Cross button does not work properly under rapid clicks</li>
	<li>On clicking confirm, user is navigated to <b>order description page unexpectedly</b></li>
</ul>


<h2><a name="ExpectedResult%3A"></a>Expected Result:</h2>

<ul>
	<li>Cross button should consistently close the popup even on rapid clicks</li>
	<li>No unintended navigation should occur</li>
	<li>System should handle multiple rapid clicks gracefully (debounce/disable)</li>
</ul>


<h2><a name="Severity%3A"></a>Severity:</h2>

<p><b>Medium → High</b></p>
            <br/>
        </td>
